ntent\",\n    \"interpretation\": \"Fix the second LLM extension prompt's false claim that the learner 'learned that scaled dot-product attention is a bank of similarity meters' this session; reframe it as a forward-stretch preview ('next session's machine, if you want a preview tonight') grounded in what was actually taught.\",\n    \"alternative\": \"Replace the prompt entirely with one about tonight's content (the plain dot product / the length problem).\",\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\",\n    \"miss\": { \"critic\": \"sam\", \"artifact\": \"ext\" }\n  },\n  {\n    \"noteId\": \"n05\",\n    \"kind\": \"style-amendment\",\n    \"confidence\": \"high\",\n    \"miss\": { \"critic\": \"none\" },\n    \"styleAmendment\": {\n      \"rule\": \"A prediction prompt must ask something the learner does not yet know; if an earlier beat already revealed the answer, sharpen the prompt to a new quantity, direction, or boundary case rather than re-asking the known.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Prediction earns its cost only when the learner cannot already answer; re-asking a revealed fact is theater across any beat, so this generalizes beyond a single fix.\"\n    }\n  }\n]\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4155,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4155},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"512f281b-cf86-4e75-b730-b2857805a59a","uuid":"d70a975a-9a5d-4b27-ad6b-416f85c13ef2","request_id":"req_011CciSbq5hit5GBDfFdDo4q"}
